        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 7 at 3:21PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 321 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Elkton, or 10 miles south of Caseville. This thunderstorm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bad Axe, Port Austin, Pigeon, Elkton, Kinde, Owendale, Verona,
Pinnebog, Port Crescent State Park, Filion, Rapson, and Bay Port.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
